MDB(Million Dollar Baby, Million Dollar Babies)
⭐️ CEO Freestyle
An originally unreleased freestyle made sometime during 2007, as confirmed by lyrics in the song, likely around the time Rocky was in MDB and joined the A$AP Mob titled "CEO Freestyle". The freestyle was eventually released online by Rocky on December 19th, 2011, but as of now it is unknown exactly where Rocky released this track online. The track has an early 2000s sound as the song was made much prior to when Rocky would find his own style many years later as this is currently the oldest full Rocky song available to the public. During the intro and hook of the freestyle the song samples "Stand Up" by Ludacris by using Ludacris' verse, but pitched down.

⭐️ Lemonade(with A$AP Rocky, A$AP Ant, A$AP Bari, A$AP Dom, A$AP Ferg, A$AP Illz, A$AP Nast & A$AP Twelvyy) (prod. Bangladesh)
Recorded on February 13th, 2010. Over nine minutes long with verses from nearly all members of the A$AP Mob, including those who don't usually rap. Uses the instrumental to, and is titled after "Lemonade" by Gucci Mane. Possibly meant for the A$AP mixtape. Randomly leaked on August 24th, 2012 by an obscure SoundCloud account, and wasn't discovered until thirteen years later when the song was offered as a bonus to the "Canary Bricks" groupbuy. Higher quality file leaked on June 19th, 2025 as part of said groupbuy.
✨ Been Around The World [V1/OG File](prod. Sunny J Beats)
OG Filename: Been Around The World OG File sent by A$AP Yams to DJ DP in an email on October 15th, 2010 asking to have the song chopped and screwed. Just five days later on October 20th, 2010 DJ DP sent the finished "Been Around The World (Slow Lane Remix)" and A$AP Yams uploaded the song to his HarlemzMostHated YouTube channel the same day. Leaked by KILLRITE on January 2nd, 2024.

Lana Del Rey - Ice Cream [V1](prod. Stevie Aiello & The Kickdrums)(My Bitch, Ridin')
Lana Del Rey song from 2010 that would eventually be reworked into the song "My Bitch". This version of the song features a completely different beat produced by The Kickdrums and Stevie Aiello, The song also has lyrics that would later be reused in a later version of the song that would feature Rocky and also have a new instrumental. While the song had long been speculated to exist, its title was officially confirmed by an insider on December 21, 2023. The full lyrics were shared by insiders on April 1, 2024, accompanied by a one-second looped snippet. On July 4, a second snippet leaked, shortly followed by the song leaking in full. In a YouTube comment, The Kickdrums revealed that the song could be considered an outtake of Born to Die and was scrapped for being "more pop" and after being shown the video for "Video Games", the song was reworked into "Ridin'".
HarlemzMostHated(with A$AP Yams)
⭐️ Been Around The World (Slow Lane Remix) [V1/OG File](with DJ DP) (prod. Sunny J Beats)
OG Filename: Been Around The World (Slow Lane Remix) An official 'Slow Lane Remix' done by DJ DP to the song "Been Around The World" which was originally released on May 10th, 2010. The song was first sent to DJ DP by someone "on Rocky's team", who is rumored to be A$AP Yams, on October 15th, 2010 requesting for the song to be remixed along with stating the song would have a cover art with DJ DP's name on it, then the freshly-made remix was sent back to that person on October 20th, 2010 and was uploaded to A$AP Yams' HarlemzMostHated YouTube channel on the same day. The remix was completely lost until it resurfaced by KILLRITE on January 1st, 2024 with the OG file leaking on January 2nd, 2024 along with the OG file for the non-remix version of the song also by KILLRITE. The remix was reused as track eleven intended for the May 16th, 2011 copy of the May 16th, 2011 copy of Rocky's "Mouth Fulla Gold" mixtape along with the original song, these were the only 2010 songs on the mixtape. The files that were used on that copy of the album were leaked by KILLRITE and Zanthin on July 18th, 2024 as a part of the successful $250 groupbuy for the "Mouth Fulla Gold" mixtape.
👑 Bittersweet Symphony Part 2(prod. The Verve & Youth)
Re-recorded version of the original "Bittersweet Symphony" which was posted on the HarlemzMostHated YouTube channel on October 23rd, 2010. Compared to the original, this song features a more upbeat flow and a few minor lyric changes, but features the same instrumental and sample of "Bitter Sweet Symphony". The outro is an interpolation of a Christian 18th century children's bedtime prayer known as "Now I Lay Me Down to Sleep" with some of the same wording changed from the previous version. After the song was released the original 'part one' of the song was used on the famous fan-made compilation "Deep Purple" by PureBakingSoda instead of this version for unknown reasons. Both versions of the song have been known as "New York Bittersweet Symphony" due to it being titled that on "Deep Purple". This is likely due to a language barrier as the creator is from France. The said miscommunication is from the original upload of "Bittersweet Symphony", the version that appeared on "Deep Purple", was listed as "Rocky ASAPNew York - Bittersweet Symphony", with the New York being an indicator of where Rocky is from, but the "New York Bittersweet Symphony" stuck due to the popularity of the compilation, but it was never officailly the title at any point.
⭐️ Uptown(feat. A$AP Nast & A$AP Twelvyy)
The track "Uptown" was released on the HarlemzMostHated YouTube channel on May 28th, 2010. The song is featured on the notorious fake mixtape "Deep Purple" along with many other songs from this era. The song features A$AP Nast and A$AP Twelvyy who went by TY Nast and Two Twelve Mel respectively at the time. The track samples Lil Wayne on "Uptown" from Drake's 2009 mixtape "So Far Gone" which shares the name with the sample used on the song by Billy Joel "Uptown Girl".
Purple Swagg(Purple Swag)
⭐️️ Feeling Good [V1](prod. A$AP Ty Beats)
Throwaway track titled "Feeling Good" that was teased by A$AP Ty Beats in 2017 as a new Rocky song he would release with the song being privately uploaded to the A$AP Mob SoundCloud on March 12th, 2017 with the same cover art shared by A$AP Ty Beats, so it was likely scrapped as a loosie, likely similar to the "Wavy Wednesdays" series, but then the full song was leaked randomly not too long before the release of "Cozy Tapes: Vol. 2: Too Cozy" on June 7th, 2017, which led to many people to think it was for that album but that is not the case. The song is almost definitely an early Rocky track due to his voice, similar flows and adlibs present in other tracks from this era but was likely made in 2010 based on when Rocky and A$AP Ty Beats met. The song interpolates Rocky's 2010 song "Been Around The World", with the line "it doesn't really matter to me". The "mouth fulla golds, nigga I got hella hoes" line was later reused for Rocky's feature on the song "4 Loko" by Smoke DZA. Rizz sound.

👑 My Bitch [V3](feat. Lana Del Rey) (prod. The Kickdrums)(Ice Cream, Ridin')
Samples "And I Panicked" by The Dramatics and interpolates "Be My Daddy" by Lana Del Rey. Rocky stated that the song would not appear on his album as people were too familiar with it, but he still wanted to release it, possibly as a single. The song leaked in full on DDotOmen on June 27th, 2012 and one day later Rocky went to Twitter to discredit the song, stating it was a "freestyle reference" with his bars being "wack af" and claiming The Kickdrums leaked the song themselves, which is backed up by a Tweet from them posted on March 5th, 2012, where they said they would leak the song despite Rocky wanting it on his album and not having time for "industry BS". The Kickdrums later denied being involved in the song's leak and never worked with Rocky again.

What’s everyone passed out for? Did you guys have a party or some shit?”. This is also when Tyler was introduced to Lil Yachty as he said “Who’s that guy with the red hair? He sounds like André 3000!” Rocky then said, “That’s Lil Yachty.” He then said, “Lil what?”. Rocky then played "Telephone Calls", and Tyler was interested in the song and looped the “Telephone call from young Carti, said it’s lit” as Rocky revealed he did not record his verse at this point. They then went across the street and recorded Tyler's verse and Rocky likely recorded his as well. There was a snippet of the song played on December 25th, 2015 and this is likely the original version without Tyler, The Creator along with Rocky's verse, but it's unconfirmed.

⭐️ Stole Ya Flow [V2](prod. ICYTWAT & Kelvin Krash)(All Black (Stole Ya Flow))
The live premiere of the song "Stole Ya Flow" at Rocky's Rolling Loud Miami performance on July 23rd, 2023, after the song's instrumental was briefly previewed in a quickly deleted Instagram post from a month before on June 7th, 2023, where it was unknown if it was an album snippet at the time. After the loud and harsh synth instrumental heard in the original snippet, lyrics can be heard stating "first you stole my flow, so I stole your bitch", with the song being an obvious diss track to one of Rihanna's ex-romantic-partners, which has since been confirmed to be Toronto artist Drake, who is a former collaborator of Rocky's, who had romantic chemistry with Rihanna throughout the 2010s. The following line speaks states, "then you stole my style, need atleast like 10%", claiming Drake has also stolen his style along with his flow. This diss track predates the infamous Drake and Kendrick Lamar beef, with Rocky going deeper into topics about Drake in later versions of the song, much of which Kendrick Lamar also mentioned during their battle.

⭐️🏆 Stop Snitching [V3](feat. BossMan Dlow) (prod. Hitkidd & Kelvin Krash)(All The Way Down, Old Jim Jones)
A finished and reworked version of the song previously previewed in 2023 known as "All The Way Down", with an updated title being "Stop Snitchin" performed live during Rocky's Rolling Loud Los Angeles performance on March 16th, 2025. During the start of the preview, Rocky says the new title of the song, mentioning it is also known as "Old Jim Jones". The song features revamped production and a new intro, using the sample "Give Love a Try" by Leroy Hutson which is also used throughout the track. An unheard feature is provided by Florida rapper BossMan Dlow, with any signs of Yoshi24k's contributions to the song not being heard. The track also removes a verse from a song, the one in which was heard in the original 2023 snippets, which is how the song became wanted by the community in the first place, and it is currently unknown why it was removed. During the performance, Rocky lifts up his shirt to reveal another shirt with a big stop sign as well as saying "STOP SNITCHIN", which is referenced in the song when he says "bout to buy a stop sign shirt to stop the snitchin", with the obvious intention as a diss towards people snitching in general as well as former A$AP Mob member Relli. The two went to trial with due to a November 2021 altercation where Rocky was accused of shooting Relli during an argument in Hollywood, with Rocky being found not guilty on all charges three years later. The general consensus of the trial is that Relli's motive was to get money from Rocky as he would often lie about the altercation during his testimony, meaning Relli was 'snitching', in this case, for money.

Your Honor [V1](prod. Metro Boomin)
An earlier unmixed version of the song "Your Honor" randomly shared on X, shortly after Rocky's not guilty verdict, by the popular hip-hop focused social media page NFR Podcast on February 25th, 2025, reposting a video from the account @mediaacct0313 claiming it is a new snippet for "DON'T BE DUMB" with production by Metro Boomin, with no title attached, only a cover art of Rocky in the court room with a parental advisory logo. The snippet talks about Rocky's time in court, where he would wear Ray-Bans and Prada in court. At the end of the snippet, Rocky says "probably got a prop on me right now", referring to his court case where he claimed he was carrying a prop gun. When the snippet was posted most of the community believed the snippet to be fake or AI due to the instrumental sounding very similar to another Metro Boomin song, "Superhero (Hereos & Villains)", and Rocky's voice sounding very rough. It was a debate whether or not the snippet was real until March 15th, 2025 when Rocky would surprisingly play the song during his Rolling Loud Los Angeles set, leaving many fans shocked. It is rumored that NFR Podcast was supplied and tasked to leak the "Your Honor" snippet to promote the album.
